Package: parade
Type: Package
Title: Declarative Parallel Dataflow with Future/Furrr
Version: 0.11.0
Authors@R: c(person(given = "Parade", family = "Authors", role = c("aut","cre"), email = "parade@example.org"))
Description: Declarative, lazy, compositional dataflow for R on top of 'future'/'furrr', with
  typed schemas, artifacts, diagnostics, and HPC-friendly distribution (local, Slurm via
  'future.batchtools'/'batchtools', and mirai for high-performance parallel execution).
  Adds an ergonomic SLURM layer: generic script submission from R, live CPU/memory monitors,
  multi-job dashboards, and now site/project defaults with NA-as-omit semantics and profiles.
  Mirai backend provides unlimited parallelism, SSH tunneling, and TLS security. Configure once,
  run everywhere.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports: tibble, tidyr, purrr, rlang, vctrs, furrr, future, progressr, glue, jsonlite, digest
Suggests: knitr, rmarkdown, future.batchtools, batchtools, mirai, future.mirai, nanonext, testthat
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2.9000
URL: https://bbuchsbaum.github.io/parade/
